post_text:
The weekend is almost here and so is the deadline for submitting your photos for Operation OJR Spirit. Here is a peek at the district-wide mass door/lawn/house decorating event. Use your creativity and show your Wildcat pride! It doesn’t have to be anything extensive, but could simply be decorating your door, even doing chalk-art on the driveway or chalk paint on windows. Plant some red and white flowers or hang some red and white balloons! Do you have any Owen J. Roberts spirit wear? Wear that and pose for a shot!? Red and white should be the theme any way you’d like to do it.

When you’ve completed your Operation OJR Spirit creation, snap a picture and click on the link below to upload your picture or if that doesn't work, email Amy Christman at achristman@ojrsd.net by no later than June 1st. These pictures will be compiled together for a last-day-of school video! If posting your phone on social media, use #operationOJRspirit.

https://photos.app.goo.gl/5iciJjWSHsocgjr86

The Chester County Health Department is seeking volunteers to assist with the COVID-19 drive-up testing site that will open at the Owen J. Roberts High School on June 1. No medical experience is necessary as they are seeking assistance with:

greeting people
traffic control
data entry

With the school year slowly coming to a close, it’s time to celebrate ALL of our students, faculty, and staff!

Let’s show our Owen J. Roberts spirit district-wide in a mass door/lawn/house decorating event. Use your creativity and show your Wildcat pride! It doesn’t have to be anything extensive, but could simply be decorating your door, even doing chalk-art on the driveway or chalk paint on windows. Plant some red and white flowers or hang some red and white balloons! Do you have any Owen J. Roberts spirit wear? Wear that and pose for a shot!? Red and white should be the theme any way you’d like to do it.

When you’ve completed your Operation OJR Spirit creation, snap a picture and click on the link below to upload your picture or if that doesn't work, email Amy Christman at achristman@ojrsd.net by no later than June 1st. These pictures will be compiled together for a last-day-of school video! If posting your phone on social media, use #operationOJRspirit.

post_text: What a beautiful week! Video will premiere at 6:30 p.m. on June 5, 2020, just as was planned for “traditional” commencement ceremonies, with access whenever you like to be viewed as many times as you like once premiered. The video link will be posted in multiple places on the district website and will be shared out on multiple social media platforms—please feel free to share the link when you see it. PCTV will be airing as well—stay tuned for times (PCTV plans to show area graduation videos 24/7 for an entire month.)

May 14 at 8:18 PM ·

During Teacher Appreciation Week OJR teachers and retirees decided that they wanted to give!
REA collected nearly $7,000 for various community groups who are helping people affected by Covid-19. Today REA President Mark DeFusco, Treasurer John Sands, and Chief Negotiator Karin Suzadail presented a check to Tara Vaszily of the Southeastern Veterans Center in Spring City for the Residents’ Welfare Fund.

post_text:
The 2020 Owen J. Roberts High School Ledger Yearbooks Are On Their Way!

If you ordered your Ledger by May 8th we have good news! Your yearbook is on its way to your house! The yearbook will be delivered via U.S. Postal Service shortly. Keep an eye out for it!

Didn't order a yearbook? All is not lost! There are a small amount of yearbooks left unsold. If you are interested contact Mr. Schwenk to reserve one of the left overs. The price is $73.00. Payment and pick up details for these extra books will be released in the coming days.

post_text:
Dear OJR Community,

There will be parties again soon, and family gatherings. There will be parades and sporting events and concerts. To help our communities when they come back together after the COVID-19 pandemic, I’m asking you to please respond to the 2020 Census now. Spend a few minutes online today to impact the next 10 years of funding on education, healthcare, and infrastructure. We all see how important these are today. So please go to https://www.2020census.gov/ and respond today to make America’s tomorrow brighter

Wishing you and your family good health and happiness!

Sincerely,

Dr. Susan T. Lloyd

Superintendent of Schools

post_text: Have you seen the red, white, & gray OJRSD vans on district roads during the statewide school closure? Those vans are our food delivery crew assuring families have food & other essentials. Families in need should contact their child school counselors for assistance. post_text:
Coventry Food Pantry is in need of certain foods and household donations at this time including:

- canned meats (tuna, ham, chicken)
- beef stew
- chili
- canned pastas
- granola bars/breakfast bars
- juice
- toilet paper
- paper towels
- antibacterial wipes and cleaning sprays
- hand sanitizers

We have been scheduling drop-off times at the Pantry each week, as needed, to accept donations. Please check https://www.facebook.com/coventryfoodpantry/ for more information. During drop-off times, we ask you to please unload donations on the pallets outside of the Pantry doors and observe the recommended social distancing standards.

The Chester County Health Department would like to clarify the following information about COVID-19:

* The Chester County Health Department does not test for COVID-19. The state laboratory is located in Chester County to serve the entire state.

* If health care providers need to report a suspected or confirmed case of COVID-19, they are to complete a clinical evaluation and call the Disease Investigation and Surveillance Team.

post_text: Owen J. Roberts received $35,000 to be used to enhance computer science education.
shared_text:
Senator Katie Muth
January 17 at 3:40 PM ·

$175,000 is coming to SD-44❗️

PAsmart has approved targeted grants for five school districts in the 44th District:

💻 Coatesville Area School District
💻 Owen J. Roberts School District
💻 Perkiomen Valley School District
💻 Phoenixville Area School District
💻 Twin Valley School District

Each district will receive $35,000 to enhance and further expand computer science classes and teacher training.

This grant will also provide the opportunity to propel students into the future and ensure their skills are on par for in-demand jobs. Congratulations to the five school districts 💪
text:
Owen J. Roberts received $35,000 to be used to enhance computer science education.

On this day, we honor the progress that has been made in special education as well as those who work in the field

post_text: Thank you for coming to the Owen J. Roberts High School Veterans Day ceremony, Senator Muth. Our gratitude is also extended to Representative Tim Hennessey for his attendance.
shared_text:
Senator Katie Muth
November 7, 2019 at 11:10 PM ·

What an amazing day at the Veterans’ Expo! 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸 A huge THANK YOU to the veterans, their families, the vendors, my colleagues, the MISSION BBQ team, the Owen J. Roberts School District color guard, and the SD44 Team that made this event awesome!

🇺🇸It is important for veterans to know about the services and programs available to them. They volunteered to serve our country and it is important that we serve them in our communities. I look forward to hosting this event again and having the opportunity to spend time with some more of America’s heroes. 🇺🇸

Roberts School District on Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACEs) and the effects of toxic stress and trauma on children and teens. As a member of the Chester County ACEs Coalition, she is a strong advocate for improving child welfare and well-being in our local communities and beyond!

Sheri provides services at The Brightening Center as a member of our Interdisciplinary Care Team, including individual and family sessions, as well as support groups. Tonight she'll be hosting our Bi-Weekly Adoption Support Group for parents of adoptive children. Message our page or call us at 610-889-0990 for more information.

post_text: Today is the 23rd annual Operation Safe Stop conducted in communities across the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania as part of National School Bus Safety Week. Thank you to local law enforcement for help with this program.
text: Today is the 23rd annual Operation Safe Stop conducted in communities across the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania as part of National School Bus Safety Week. Thank you to local law enforcement for help with this program.

post_text:
Each year Owen J Roberts uses over 90 school buses and vans to transport almost 6,100 students to and from school each school day traveling nearly 1.5 million miles a year.

On Wednesday, Oct. 23, 2019, the 23rd annual Operation Safe Stop will be conducted in communities across the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania as part of National School Bus Safety Week, which runs Oct. 21-25. The Owen J Roberts School District, along with local law enforcement and Gross School Bus Company, will be participating in the 23rd annual Operation Safe Stop. Thank you to all who work to keep our roadways and our children safe!

post_text:
This meeting is a follow-up to the September 30th School Board Pupil Services Committee public meeting in which board members reviewed the delayed start options, timeline, and cost analysis of each option. The three options discussed include:
• Hybrid/Online model in which secondary students could, by choice, flex their schedule and come in later to school. There were 3 transportation models for this option with associated costs
• Delayed start model for all students. Secondary 8AM and Elementary 9AM. There is one transportation model with associated costs
• No Change. All start times would stay the same.

To better understand how the options were developed, current research, options details, costs, timeline, etc – please check out the pupil services website with all related information. https://www.ojrsd.com/Page/8901

post_text: Happy Constitution Day! East Coventry Elementary students were part of this annual celebration.
shared_text:
Chester County Intermediate Unit is at Chester County Courthouse.
September 17, 2019 at 5:55 PM · West Chester, PA ·

Students from various Chester County schools gathered together at the historic West Chester courthouse to celebrate Constitution Day and the Kids Voting Kickoff ceremony today. They participated in a mock voter registration, and learned about the importance of voting and what being a citizen means.

Attendees heard from CCIU executive director Dr. George Fiore, Senator Andy Dinniman, County Commissioner Michelle Kichline, County Commissioner Terence Farrell, County Commissioner Kathi Cozzone and Benjamin Franklin himself!

Thanks to everyone who joined us on this beautiful day. 🇺🇸

post_text: Help extend a warm welcome to the newest Owen J. Roberts teachers, who will spend the week getting set up with everything they need to welcome students on August 26. Their week kicked off with plenty of engaging activities, including teamwork practice in a well-designed escape room! These are the BEST and BRIGHTEST, and we are thrilled to welcome each of them to the Wildcat family!
